type="user">jms-009Q</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-009Q.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Forester 2.5">Forester 2.5</fr:title><fr:taxon>Release</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Thanks to <fr:link
href="dannypsnl.xml"
title="Lîm Tsú-thuàn"
addr="dannypsnl"
type="local">Lîm Tsú-thuàn</fr:link> and <fr:link
href="vikramanchoudhury.xml"
title="Vikraman Choudhury"
addr="vikramanchoudhury"
type="local">Vikraman Choudhury</fr:link> for their suggestions and bug reports on the <fr:link
href="https://lists.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-discuss"
type="external">mailing list</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:ul><fr:li>A new <fr:code><![CDATA[\iftex]]></fr:code> command has been added, following a suggestion of <fr:link
href="vikramanchoudhury.xml"
title="Vikraman Choudhury"
addr="vikramanchoudhury"
type="local">Vikraman Choudhury</fr:link>; this can be used to control the behavior of macros, depending on whether they are being rendered by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\LaTeX ]]></fr:tex> or by the browser. For example, <fr:code><![CDATA[\iftex{foo}{bar}]]></fr:code> will become <fr:code>foo</fr:code> when passed to the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\LaTeX ]]></fr:tex> tool, but will be reated as <fr:code>bar</fr:code> when rendering for the browser.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>A new <fr:link
href="jms-005O.xml"
title="Forester 2.1"
addr="jms-005O"
type="local">fluid binding</fr:link> <fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/taxon]]></fr:code> has been added to the <fr:link
href="jms-0067.xml"
title="Forester 2.2 › flexible transclusion options"
addr="jms-0067"
type="local">transclusion overrides</fr:link>, which can be used to locally change the taxon of a transcluded tree. Thanks to <fr:link
href="dannypsnl.xml"
title="Lîm Tsú-thuàn"
addr="dannypsnl"
type="local">Lîm Tsú-thuàn</fr:link> for implementing this.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>In order to support more modular development of <fr:link
href="tfmt-000V.xml"
title="Forests of evergreen notes"
addr="tfmt-000V"
type="local">forests</fr:link>, a new <fr:code>theme</fr:code> directory is expected to contain all the XSL, CSS, font, etc. assets that pertain to the <fr:em>presentation</fr:em> of your <fr:link
href="tfmt-000V.xml"
title="Forests of evergreen notes"
addr="tfmt-000V"
type="local">forest</fr:link>; the <fr:code>assets</fr:code> directory is meant to store things like images, PDFs, etc. that pertain to the <fr:em>content</fr:em> of your <fr:link
href="tfmt-000V.xml"
title="Forests of evergreen notes"
addr="tfmt-000V"
type="local">forest</fr:link>. The simplest way to take advantage of this new feature is to bind your <fr:code>theme</fr:code> directory to a <fr:link
href="https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Tools-Submodules"
type="external">git submodule</fr:link> pointing to the <fr:link
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-base-theme"
type="external">forester-base-theme</fr:link> repository. Your existing <fr:link
href="tfmt-000V.xml"
title="Forests of evergreen notes"
addr="tfmt-000V"
type="local">forest</fr:link> will still work fine for now even if you do not migrate to the new directory structure. I’m grateful to <fr:link
href="arma%C3%ABlgu%C3%A9neau.xml"
title="Armaël Guéneau"
addr="armaëlguéneau"
type="local">Armaël Guéneau</fr:link> for conversations that motivated me to make this change.</fr:li></fr:ul></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
